title: the cartesian product: type theory vs. set theory

media:group.media:title: the cartesian product: type theory vs. set theory
media:group.media:description:
When I was reading through Section 1.5 on the Homotopy Type Theory book, I was initially very confused as to what was going one, particularly regarding the uniqueness principle. I don't go into detail about the constructions they provide in the chapter, but hopefully this will be a helpful overview of what is going on intuitively.
